## Push Summary — skrptiq-cli (main)

### What shipped
Replaced readline with bubbletea inline mode for the prompt. This gives us the Claude Code-style layout:

- **Managed region at bottom**: separator + textarea + separator + status bar (4+ lines)
- **tea.Println() for scrollback**: all output goes above the managed region permanently
- **Separators only around active prompt**: they're part of the bubbletea View(), redrawn each frame, never in scrollback
- **Status bar below prompt**: mode, profile, provider — always visible
- **tea.WithInputTTY()**: reliable key input
- **Ctrl+C/D/Esc**: intercepted before textarea sees them
- **Multi-line wrapping**: textarea expands up to 8 lines

### Architecture
```
internal/prompt/prompt.go — minimal bubbletea model (separator + textarea + separator + status)
internal/app/app.go       — top-level model wrapping prompt, all command handlers
main.go                   — creates program with tea.WithInputTTY(), no alt screen
```

